=====Usage notes=====
* {{m|en|thou|Thou}} is used with the archaic second-person singular of verbs, which usually ends in {{m|en|-est}}, as in, for example, “Lovest '''thou''' me?” Irregular forms include: {{term|art}} (of {{m|en|be}}), {{term|hast}} (of {{m|en|have}}), {{m|en|shalt}} (of {{m|en|shall}}), {{m|en|wost}} (of {{term|wit}}), {{m|en|wilt}} (of {{term|will}}), and {{m|en|dost}} (of {{m|en|do}}).
* Many old uses of ''thou'' and ''ye'' followed the [[w:T-V distinction|T-V distinction]], ''thou'' being the informal pronoun.

